beton-mvp/
- config.ini
- requirements.txt
- run.py
- app/
  - __init__.py
  - config.py
  - models.py
  - routes_materials.py
  - templates/
    - base.html
    - materials.html
- migrations/  <- created by `flask db init`

config.ini holds all details: host, port, user, password, database, schema, table.

config.py reads these values and forms DB_URI, MATERIALS_TABLE and MATERIALS_SCHEMA.

models.py defines Material = Table(...) using reflection (autoload_with=db.engine).

routes_materials.py uses core-style Material.select(), .delete() and .insert() without touching column names in code.
